#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:11 viewer.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Viewer"
msgstr "Näitamisaken"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The reason for you to put all your images into &kphotoalbum;, and spending "
"hours after hours describing them, is of course that you at some point want "
"to look at them. For that purpose &kphotoalbum; has an viewer capable of "
"showing your images and videos. You open the viewer from the thumbnail view "
"as described in <xref linkend=\"chp-thumbnail-view\"/>."
msgstr ""
" Põhjus, miks kasutada &kphotoalbum;it ja kulutada pikki tunde pilte "
"kirjeldades, on mõistagi see, et ühel hetkel tahad sa neid pilte ka näha. "
"Selleks pakub &kphotoalbum; näitamisakent, mille saab avada sirvimisaknast, "
"nagu kirjeldab <xref linkend=\"chp-thumbnail-view\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "Common Viewer Commands"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:21
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The viewer supports both images and videos. The following commands are "
"supported for both images and videos:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Press <keycap>Esc</keycap> to close the viewer window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press either <keycap>Page Down</keycap> or the <keycap>Space</keycap> bar to "
"move to the next image or video, and press <keycap>Page Up</keycap> to move "
"to the previous image or video."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo> to open the <link "
"linkend=\"chp-typingIn\">annotation dialog</link> for the current image or "
"video."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>4</keycap></keycombo> to set the image or "
"video as the first in its stack (if it is already part of a stack)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>d</keycap></keycombo> to edit the image "
"description."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press either <keycap>&Enter;</keycap> or <keycap>F11</keycap> to toggle full "
"screen mode while viewing an image or video."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <keycap>Delete</keycap> to remove the current image or video from the "
"viewer list (as if you hadn't selected it for viewing) and advance to the "
"next item in the viewer list. If the last image or video in the viewer list "
"is removed, the viewer window is closed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>Delete</keycap></keycombo> to add the current "
"image or video to the viewer's deletion list. When the viewer window is "
"closed, &kphotoalbum; will open the <emphasis>Removing Items</emphasis> "
"dialog if the deletion list is not empty."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:80
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Drawing on Images"
msgid "Viewing Images"
msgstr "Pildiosa valimine"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <xref linkend=\"sect-viewer-common-commands\"/> for viewer commands "
"supported for both images and videos."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:86
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The viewer can be seen in <xref linkend=\"fig-viewer\"/>. The viewer does "
#| "of course show you the image, but in addition to that it also shows you "
#| "the information you specified for each image, including, who is on the "
#| "images, where and when it was takes, &etc;"
msgid ""
"The viewer can be seen in <xref linkend=\"fig-viewer\"/>. The viewer does of "
"course show you the image, but in addition to that it also shows you the "
"information you specified for each image, including who is in the image, "
"where and when it was taken, &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Näitamisakent näitab <xref linkend=\"fig-viewer\"/>. Mõistagi näitab see "
"sulle sinu pilti, kuid lisaks sellele ka infot, mille oled pildi kohta "
"määranud, sealhulgas seda, kes on pildil, millal ja kus see on tehtud jne."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Info Box"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The viewer provides an info box which can be overlaid on top of the image. "
"The info box is positioned at the bottom center in <xref linkend=\"fig-viewer"
"\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the info box is located on top of part of the image you actually want to "
"see, you can click the &LMB; on the info box and drag it elsewhere on the "
"image. Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>i</keycap></keycombo> to toggle the "
"info box on or off."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:115
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In case the info box is located on top of part of the images you actually "
#| "want to see, you can simply grab it with the mouse, and move it elsewhere "
#| "on the image. It is possible to configure what should be shown in the "
#| "info box, and of course whether it should be shown at all. All these "
#| "options are available by right clicking your mouse on the viewer. The "
#| "context menu can be seen in <xref linkend=\"fig-viewer-contextmenu\"/> "
#| "below."
msgid ""
"It is possible to configure what should be shown in the info box, and of "
"course whether it should be shown at all. All these options are available by "
"clicking the &RMB; on the viewer. The context menu can be seen in <xref "
"linkend=\"fig-viewer-contextmenu\"/> below."
msgstr ""
"Kui infokast asub pildi sellise osa peal, mida sa näha tahad, võid haarata "
"kastist hiirega ja lohistada selle kuhugi mujale. Võimalik on määrata, "
"millist infot kastis näidatakse, ja mõistagi saab määrata ka seda, kas "
"infokasti üldse näidatakse. Kõiki neid võimalusi saab kasutada hiire parema "
"nupuga näitamisaknal klõpsates. Kontekstimenüüd näitab <xref linkend=\"fig-"
"viewer-contextmenu\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "The viewer's context menu"
msgstr "Näitamisakna kontekstimenüü"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:130
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Some of the words in the info box is underlines. If you click the mouse "
#| "on one of these words the browser (see <xref linkend=\"chp-browsing\"/>) "
#| "will go into scope of that item. Thus if you click on <literal>Anne "
#| "Helene</literal> the browser will show you all images of Anne Helene, "
#| "just as it would have done if you selected <literal>People</literal> from "
#| "the root of the browser, and next selected <literal>Anne Helene</literal>."
msgid ""
"Some of the words in the info box are underlined. If you click the &LMB; on "
"one of these words, the browser (see <xref linkend=\"chp-browsing\"/>) will "
"go into the scope of that item. For example, in the demo if you click on "
"<literal>Anne Helene</literal> in the info box, the browser will show you "
"all images of Anne Helene, just as it would have done if you selected "
"<literal>People</literal> from the root of the browser, and next selected "
"<literal>Anne Helene</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Mõningad sõnad infokastis on alla joonitud. Kui mõnel sellisel sõnal hiirega "
"klõpsata, avab sirvimisaken (vaata <xref linkend=\"chp-browsing\"/>) antud "
"sõnaga seotud pildid. Kui näiteks klõpsata sõnal <literal>Anne Helene</"
"literal>, näitab sirvimisaken kõiki Anne Helene pilte - otsekui oleksid "
"valinud sirvimisaknas <literal>Inimesed</literal> ja seejärel <literal>Anne "
"Helene</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:138
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In the info box you can see a small button with the &kphotoalbum; logo. "
#| "Pressing that button will get you to the thumbnail viewer. The thumbnail "
#| "view will display all images, and the image you just had in the viewer "
#| "will be selected. The idea behind this is the following: you browse to a "
#| "given person, and look at the images of that person. One of the images is "
#| "from say your high school time, and now you want to see images from that "
#| "period of time. Using the <guilabel>Jump to Context</guilabel> button, "
#| "you are brought to the thumbnail view showing all images, with the "
#| "current one being in focus, and likely all your high school pictures "
#| "around it."
msgid ""
"In the top right-hand corner of the info box you can see a small "
"<emphasis>Jump to Context</emphasis> button with the &kphotoalbum; logo. "
"Clicking the &LMB; on this button will navigate to the <xref linkend=\"chp-"
"thumbnail-view\"/>. The thumbnail view will display all images, and the "
"image you just had in the viewer will be selected. The idea behind this is "
"the following: you browse to a given person, and look at the images of that "
"person. One of the images is from say your high school time, and now you "
"want to see images from that period of time. Using the <guilabel>Jump to "
"Context</guilabel> button, you are brought to the thumbnail view showing all "
"images, with the current one being in focus and likely all your high school "
"pictures around it."
msgstr ""
"Infokastis näeb ka väikest &kphotoalbum;i logoga nuppu. Sellele vajutades "
"avatakse pisipiltide näitaja. Pisipildivaates näidatakse kõiki pilte, see "
"pilt, mida äsja vaatasid, on valitud. Asja mõte on järgmine: uurid mõnda "
"inimest ja otsid tema pilte. Üks pilt võib olla pärit kooliajast, mis "
"tekitab sul tahtmise vaadata ka teisi samast ajast pärit pilte. Nupuga "
"<guilabel>Hüppa kontekstile</guilabel> viiaksegi sind pisipildivaatesse, kus "
"on esile tõstetud pilt, mida vaatasid, ja mille ümber näed arvatavasti just "
"teisi kooliaja pilte."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the current image has geolocation coordinates, you will see a map button "
"below the <guilabel>Jump to Context</guilabel> button in the info box. "
"Clicking the &LMB; on this button will open a new window with a map showing "
"where the photograph was taken."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The map button is only displayed if &kphotoalbum; was compiled with &marble; "
"support."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:163
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Drawing on Images"
msgid "Viewing More Images"
msgstr "Pildiosa valimine"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:164
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In case you have loaded several images into the viewer, you can go forth "
#| "and back using <keycap>Page Up</keycap> and <keycap>Page Down</keycap>. "
#| "You can go to the first and last images using <keycap>Home</keycap> and "
#| "<keycap>End</keycap>. These functions are of course also available from "
#| "the context menu."
msgid ""
"In case you have loaded several images into the viewer, in addition to "
"moving forward and backward using <keycap>Page Up</keycap> and <keycap>Page "
"Down</keycap> keys, respectively, you can go to the first and last images "
"using <keycap>Home</keycap> and <keycap>End</keycap>. These functions are of "
"course also available from the context menu."
msgstr ""
"Kui laadisid näitamisaknasse mitu pilti, saad edasi-tagasi liikuda "
"klahvidega <keycap>Page Up</keycap> ja <keycap>Page Down</keycap>. Esimesele "
"ja viimasele pildile saab liikuda vastavalt klahviga <keycap>Home</keycap> "
"ja <keycap>End</keycap>. Samad liikumisvõimalused leiab mõistagi ka "
"kontekstimenüüst."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can display multiple images as a slide show. In slide "
"show mode, &kphotoalbum; loads a new image into the viewer every few "
"seconds. Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>r</keycap></keycombo> to toggle the "
"slide show on or off. Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>+</keycap></keycombo> to "
"make the slide show go faster or <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>-</keycap></"
"keycombo> to make it go slower."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zooming In and Out"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:182
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Using the viewer, you may zoom in and out of your image, simply by "
#| "dragging out a rectangle with the mouse. Pressing the minus key will zoom "
#| "out again. Pressing the plus key will zoom in at the center of the image. "
#| "<xref linkend=\"fig-marking-zoom-rectangle\"/> below shows how a zoom "
#| "rectangle is marked, and <xref linkend=\"fig-zoomed-view\"/> shows the "
#| "result of the zoom."
msgid ""
"Using the viewer, you may zoom in and out of your image by dragging out a "
"rectangle with the &LMB;. Pressing the <keycap>minus</keycap> key will zoom "
"out again. Pressing the <keycap>plus</keycap> key will zoom in at the center "
"of the image. <xref linkend=\"fig-marking-zoom-rectangle\"/> below shows how "
"a zoom rectangle is marked, and <xref linkend=\"fig-zoomed-view\"/> shows "
"the result of the zoom."
msgstr ""
"Näitamisaknas saab pilti suurendada ja vähendada lihtsalt hiirega "
"ristkülikut joonistades. Miinusklahvile vajutamine vähendab pilti. "
"Plussklahvile vajutamine suurendab pilti. Allpool näitab <xref linkend=\"fig-"
"marking-zoom-rectangle\"/> ristküliku joonistamist ning <xref linkend=\"fig-"
"zoomed-view\"/> suurendamise tulemust."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:189
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Pressing the period key, lets you reset zooming, so the image is shown un-"
#| "zoomed. Pressing the equal sign will set the zoom level so each pixel on "
#| "the screen correspond to a pixel in the image."
msgid ""
"Press the <keycap>period</keycap> key to reset the zoom level so the image "
"is shown at its normal size. Pressing the <keycap>=</keycap> key will set "
"the zoom level so each pixel on the screen correspond to a pixel in the "
"image."
msgstr ""
"Punktiklahvile vajutades saab suurenduse lähtestada, nii et pilti näidatakse "
"taas algsel kujul. Võrdusmärgile vajutades määratakse suurendustase "
"selliseks, et igale ekraani pikslile vastab piksel pildil."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:194 viewer.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zooming in the viewer"
msgstr "Suurendamine näitamisaknas"

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:215
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
